This paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for computer vision tasks, specifically focusing on convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of reinforcement learning for automating CNN architecture search, which suggests the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) may also be relevant. Finally, the paper discusses natural language understanding, which could potentially place it in the sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language).
